"Abstract Massachusetts Institute of Technology host a laudable Web site http://web.mit.edu/ kerberos/www/ dedicated to Kerberos, the network authentication protocol designed to provide strong authentication for client/server applications by using secret-key cryptography. It provides an excellent introduction to Kerberos (not surprisingly, since it was created by MIT) with valuable links to other sites. If you are living in the US or Canada, you can download the latest version of Kerberos V5 Release 1.0.5 free of charge. This includes everything you need to set up and use Kerberos including: • • Kerberos server. • • Full-featured Kerberos administration system. • • Secure, encrypted versions of telnet, rlogin, rsh, rcp and ftp. • • Libraries needed to integrate Kerberos security into new applications."
